MySQL-Python installation
=========================
You must have the MySQL-Python module installed.
On Debian/Ubuntu, use:
	sudo apt-get install python-mysqldb

On RedHat/CentOS, use:
	sudo yum install MySQL-python

Or get it directly from:
	http://sourceforge.net/projects/mysql-python/


mycheckpoint installation
=========================
Untar the archive file. In the same path as this INSTALL file, execute:
	sudo python setup.py install

or, as user root:
	python setup.py install

On unix like systems, the script will be installed in /usr/bin/
You must have Python >= 2.4 to install this tool.

This tool has not been tested on Windows. There is currently no scheduled plan for that.
It may work, in which case do let me know!
